<article id="post-2914" class="post-2914 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-deputy-secretary-general category-secretary-general-ban-ki-moon tag-syria">
	<header class="entry-header">
		<h1 class="entry-title">Sunday update: report of UN Mission to Investigate Allegations of Use of Chemical Weapons in Syria</h1>

				<div class="entry-meta">
			<span class="sep">Posted on </span><a href="http://blogs.un.org/blog/2013/09/15/sunday-update-syria/" title="8:24 PM" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date" datetime="2013-09-15T20:24:39+00:00">September 15, 2013</time></a><span class="by-author"> <span class="sep"> by </span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://blogs.un.org/blog/author/nancygroves/" title="View all posts by Social Media Team" rel="author">Social Media Team</a></span></span>		</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
			</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	<div class="entry-content">
		<div id="attachment_2915" class="wp-caption aligncenter" style="width: 970px"><a href="http://i0.wp.com/blogs.un.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/sellstrom.jpg" ><img class=" wp-image-2915 " alt="sellstrom" src="http://i0.wp.com/blogs.un.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/sellstrom.jpg?resize=584%2C438" data-recalc-dims="1" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon and Åke Sellström, head of the chemical weapons team dealing with Syria, discuss the report on the 21 August 2013 incident with senior advisers. Also pictured are Deputy-Secretary-General Jan Eliasson, Chef de Cabinet Susana Malcorra and other members of his senior management group and staff. Photo credit: Office of the Spokesperson of the Secretary-General.</p></div>
<p>On Sunday, the <a href="http://bit.ly/17BKbmA" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','http://bit.ly/17BKbmA']);">Office of the Spokesperson for the Secretary-General issued a statement </a>on the following:</p>
<p>Professor Åke Sellström transmitted the report of the United Nations Mission to Investigate Allegations of the Use of Chemical Weapons in the Syrian Arab Republic to Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon on Sunday.  The Secretary-General will provide the report to Member States on Monday.<a title="http://bit.ly/17BKbmA" href="http://t.co/fJqGkPUBLO" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><br />
</a></p>
<p>The Secretary-General is expected to speak to the press on Monday morning after his briefing to the Security Council.</p>
<p>The text of the report will be made available tomorrow morning on the website of the<a href="http://www.un.org/disarmament/" > UN Office for Disarmament Affairs</a>.</p>
<p>On Saturday, the <a href="http://www.un.org/apps/news/story.asp?NewsID=45852&amp;Cr=syria&amp;Cr1=#.UjZOMcasiSo" >Secretary-General received Syria&#8217;s formal accession to the treaty banning chemical weapons</a>.</p>
<p>Related material</p>
